wikipedia_page.main: Lieutenant-Colonel Sir Edward Boscawen Frederick, 9th Baronet,  (29 June 1880 – 26 October 1956) was a British Army officer, first-class cricketer and courtier.

response: Frederick was the eldest son of Colonel Charles Frederick, nephew of Sir John Frederick, 4th Baronet MP. Edward's son Charles by his second wife, Mary, inherited the baronetcy as 7th baronet. His grandson, Sir Edward Frederick, 9th Baronet, was an Army officer and first-class cricketer.
